The paper discusses the use of Full Dimension (FD) multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) technology in cellular networks, which involves antenna arrays and channel modeling. This makes it likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of massive MIMO antenna arrays (cs.MM) and beamforming techniques (cs.AR), which further support these sub-categories.
